FBIS4-28950 "dreas115_c_94029" FBIS-EAS-94-115 Daily Report 12 Jun 1994 North Korea Jun Resistance Anniversary Commemorated in Seoul Jun Resistance Anniversary Commemorated in Seoul SK1206102794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0821 GMT 12 Jun 94 SK1206102794 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- Members of the National Alliance for Democracy and Reunification (Chongukyonhap) and the South Korean Federation of General Student Councils (Hanchongnyon), more than 4,000 in all, held an all-people memorial service for those who fell while fighting for the nation and democracy at the amphitheatre of the Hanyang University on June 11, a Seoul-based radio reported. In his opening address, Yi Chang-pok, permanent chairman of Chongukyonhap, charged that "the present Kim Yong-sam `government' is totally blocking democratisation and reunification" and called for an all-people movement to check "the parliamentary ratification of the final act of the Uruguay Round world trade accord" and demanded a peaceful solution to the nuclear issue of the Korean peninsula. Then, a rally marking the June resistance anniversary was held to inherit the spirit of the martyrs. The ralliers vowed to fulfil the tasks to realise a genuine democracy and independent reunification on the occasion of the 7th anniversary of the resistance.
